17/04/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The main opposition Social Democratic Party (PSD) and the Conservative Party say they plan to sign an alliance protocol Thursday (April 17th).
The parties intend to create a common parliamentary group, a common secretary general and a common delegation after the first round of local elections on June 1st.
PSD leader Mircea Geoana explained that this will be a true political alliance, not just a temporary move for the elections.
(Adevarul, Gandul, Evenimentul Zilei - 17/04/08;
Mediafax, Hotnews.ro - 16/04/08)
